<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000015#     2#          738#">Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-738</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_15.2-738"/><heading><desig>§ 15.2-738.</desig><title>Modification of grievance procedure</title></heading><bodyText><p>Notwithstanding the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-1202.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-1202.1">§§ 2.2-1202.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#       1202.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 15.2-1506"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-1506">15.2-1506<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000015#     2#         1506#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 15.2-1507"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-1507">15.2-1507<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000015#     2#         1507#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> to the contrary, in any county which has the county manager plan of government provided for in this chapter, a grievance procedure may be established which permits an Equal Employment Opportunity officer, except the Director of the Department of Human Resource Management appointed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-1200"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-1200">§ 2.2-1200<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         1200#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and any employees thereof, to be present at any step of a grievance procedure established under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 15.2-1506"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-1506">§ 15.2-1506<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000015#     2#         1506#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>. Such officer shall not be an advocate or representative on behalf of either the grievant or management.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1989 VA CH 622"><content><span normalizedCite="1989 Va. Ch. 622">1989, c. 622<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1989#000622#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 15.1-687.16; <citation normalizedCite="1991 VA CH 143"><content><span normalizedCite="1991 Va. Ch. 143">1991, c. 143<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1991#000143#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 770"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 770">1995, cc. 770<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000770#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 818"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 818">818<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000818#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1996 VA CH 164"><content><span normalizedCite="1996 Va. Ch. 164">1996, cc. 164<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="